caption.text: Tanah Lot Temple, located on the western part of Bali, is one of Indonesia‚Äôs most remarkable landmarks. Rent a scooter and enjoy the ride to this offshore Hindu temple. We took a little over an hour to get there from Ubud and arrived before sunrise. Unfortunately, you cannot enter temple grounds, but you can take advantage of the amazing panoramic view, as you see waves constantly colliding on this famous rock.

This is what it‚Äôs like to be above the clouds. No wonder this place is considered the gateway to heaven. It's filled with gorgeous historical Balinese architecture and a stunning view of one of Indonesia's most incredible volcanos, Mount Agung, the highest point of the island.

caption.text:
One of the best experiences about Asia is the close encounter you can have with wildlife animals, like the elephants. Make sure to do your research and go to preservation camps, like this one in Chiang Mai. Once you‚Äôre on your journey to the jungle, you‚Äôll spend the day at the camp feeding, bathing, playing, riding and giving them lots of love and care. Many elephant camps are abusive to animals and are money driven. The good thing about this one is that they rescue elephants from circuses, poachers and even injured or abandoned ones.
